rComments: Once you realize that she genuinely cares for her students she's an amazing prof. She doesn't sugar coat anything so if you want someone to tell you how amazing you are rather than how you can improve and be even better she is not for you. She gives plenty of feedback and is always willing to discuss anything you are concerned about.
She is wonderful! Very direct and to the point, but that's the kind of teacher you need in this field. Knowledgeable, funny and personable.

Andrea is the smartest, most knowledgeable, most hilarious prof you'll ever have. She is an amazing interviewer, she'll give you a lot of criticism, some people think she's harsh, but I guarantee I've become a better interviewer thanks to it. You will learn a lot from her feedback. I highly recommend her! You'll love her!

Quite critical when giving you "constructive feedback" during mock interviews, with minimal to no feedback about what you're doing well. She can even be mildly insulting. Be prepared for your ego to take a hit. It was bad enough that I would suggest taking a different section. Otherwise she is very experienced in the field, insightful, fair marks.
this should be family meditation not mediation. The class and the prof would be put anyone to sleep, poor family.
what can I say.. deal with issues .. course is more like family meditation than mediation.. BORING
